Package: buckethost
Type: Package
Title: Host and Catalogue Files on S3-Compatible Object Storage
Version: 0.0.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Eliot", "McIntire", email = "eliotmcintire@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("PredictiveEcology", role = c("cph", "fnd")))
Description: Tools to publish, browse, and maintain datasets on any
    S3-compatible object store (Amazon S3, OpenStack Swift, Ceph, MinIO,
    Cloudflare R2, Backblaze B2). Generates browsable, self-contained static
    HTML catalogues for a bucket; wraps 'rclone' for uploads, deletes, and
    integrity checks; and builds '/vsicurl/' URLs so Cloud-Optimized GeoTIFFs
    can be read remotely with 'GDAL' (e.g. via 'terra') without downloading
    whole files. Originally built to host open geospatial data on the Digital
    Research Alliance of Canada's Arbutus object storage.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
